===Etymology 1===
From Middle English '''[[bere]]''' from Old English '''[[bera]]'''; related to Old English '''[[brun]]''' meaning ''brown''.

====Noun====
'''bear''' (''plural:'' '''[[bears]]''')
# A large carnivorous mammal, related to the dog and racoon, having shaggy hair, a very small tail, and flat feet.
# {{colloquial}} An animal that resembles a bear, such as a [[koala]], [[panda]], or [[sloth]].  <!-- FWIW, pandas are actually in the family Ursidae -->
# {{finance}} An [[investor]] who sells in anticipation of falling prices.
# {{colloquial}} A problem that is very difficult to solve.
# {{slang}} A large hairy man, especially one who is [[gay]].

